com.camerontec.catalys.util.marketdata

Interface IFixFieldInfos

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IFieldInfos
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FixFieldInfos

    public interface IFixFieldInfos
extends IFieldInfos
    Extension of standard IFieldInfos to support FIX related mapping information from market data fields.

    getFieldInfo returns an IFixFieldInfos object.

    • Method Detail

      • getFieldID

        int getFieldID(char mdEntryType,
               int fixTag)
        Returns the Cameron market data field ID corresponding to the given FIX MDEntryType and FIX tag number.

        See FieldInfos for list of standard field IDS.

        Parameters:
        mdEntryType - FIX MDEntryType.
        fixTag - FIX Tag number.
        Returns:
        Market data field ID - 0 if unknown.

      • getMDEntryTypeIndex

        int getMDEntryTypeIndex(char mdEntryType)
        Returns the unique int index assigned to the given FIX MDEntryType. This index is suitable for efficient indexing and storage.
        Parameters:
        mdEntryType - FIX MDEntryType value.
        Returns:
        Assigned index - small non negative int. 0 if unknown.

      • getMaxMDEntryTypeIndex

        int getMaxMDEntryTypeIndex()
        Maximum MDEntryType index.
        Returns:
        Maximum index assigned to MDEntryType values.
        See Also:
        getMDEntryTypeIndex(char)

      • getMDEntryTypeFromIndex

        char getMDEntryTypeFromIndex(int mdEntryTypeIndex)
        Returns the MDEntryType values associated with the given index.

        Returns:
        MDEntryType value associated with given index.
        See Also:
        getMDEntryTypeIndex(char)

      • getSecurityStatusFieldIDArray

        int[] getSecurityStatusFieldIDArray()
        Returns the fieldIDs which are used to populate the FIX SecurityStatus message.

        FIX has three messages which can send out instrument status fields, MarketDataIncrementalRefresh and MarketDataSnapshot, plus SecurityStatus.

        Returns:
        Array of fieldIDs.

      • getSecurityStatusFieldIDSet

        SmallIntSet getSecurityStatusFieldIDSet()
        Identical to getSecurityStatusFieldIDArray() except that it returns a set, designed for rapid lookup.
        Returns:
        Set of fieldIDs.
